The article discusses President Obama's participation in a tele-town hall meeting with senior citizens to discuss new Medicare benefits and protections under the Affordable Care Act. The meeting also focused on efforts to combat senior scams and reduce waste, fraud, and abuse in Medicare. The Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) has been directed to cut the improper payment rate in half by 2012. HHS Secretary Kathleen Sebelius and Attorney General Eric Holder sent a letter to state attorneys general urging them to work with law enforcement officials to prevent scams and fraud against seniors on Medicare. A national education campaign was launched to provide information to seniors on protecting themselves from scams or fraud related to their Medicare benefits. The article also mentions the presence of elected officials and supporting organizations at the town hall meeting.